<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-210-740  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 210 740.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  March 5 1990 n457 p3(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Exodus at IBM. (IBM's early retirement offer)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Sperling, Ed.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM's early retirement offer to 10,000 employees is generatingpositive responses from nearly three times more employees thanexpected.andP;  The offer was made as part of the company'scost-cutting measures to improve profitability.andP;  Industry analystssay the number of early retirees could reach 15,000.andP;  Many ofthose who volunteered for the program are from the manufacturingsector and employees with the most seniority.andP;  IBM officials say,however, that not all who applied for early retirement will beaccepted.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (personnel management).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Topic:     RetirementEmployee BenefitsPersonnel ManagementCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>